</mei>

<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- mm. 1–2: I-V walking harmony; m2 chromatic A-natural in melody only, LH stays diatonic on V (Bb)
- mm. 3–4: Dotted rhythmic pattern in m3 mirrors melody; ii-V-I-V cycle in m4
- mm. 5–6: Dark vi color in m5 (Cm = sub for non-diatonic C-major); m6 ii with LH F4 top for wide span
- mm. 7–8: vi-iii-vi sequence for inner phrase; m8 full I-vi-ii-V cadential approach
- m9: Final I with pedal Eb1 and RH 4-note full Eb chord — maximum sonority

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- m2 beat 4: melody A-natural is chromatic passing tone; LH holds V (Bb) unchanged
- m5→m6: vi Eb3 common tone held in LH while root moves C→F (ii step up)
- m7: stepwise descending melody c-d-c (C5-D5-C5) matched by vi-iii-vi chord sequence
- m8: I-vi-ii-V complete authentic cadential bass line Eb-C-F-Bb
- m9: first and only time RH uses 4 notes (full I chord Eb-G-Bb-Eb), marking final arrival

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm. 1–2: spare, open (2-note RH, 3-note LH) — trumpet-like clarity
- mm. 3–4: adding rhythmic lift (dotted quarter feel)
- mm. 5–7: richest middle section, vi/iii color, LH 4 notes in m7
- mm. 8–9: full sonority building to pedal-reinforced final Eb chord
-->
